Review_body:
Not only is this a terrible film, but it somehow manages to be even more unbelievable than it's predecessors by having Jason beaten by a child. Jason loses to an irritating child in what was billed as his final appearance. Wtf? The irrationally high IMDB rating for this garbage is because Jason fans are irrational, and B movie fans get excited by seeing a Corey and a Crispen. I love Jason, but I will never watch this mistake again. The proof is in the pud - if this was even close to a good movie, then it really would have been 'The Final Chapter'. But it was too cheap to make, it made too much money in VHS sales, and it was way too bad to be the last appearance of Jason.You have to give Jason credit - no one ever tried harder to kill off Jason Voorhees than the writers and producers of this film. But, Jason was really hard to kill.RealReview Posting Scoring Criteria:
